<P>
Two men were arrested on suspicion of murder stemming from a gang-related 
shooting earlier this week in Pacoima, Los Angeles police said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Oliver Johnson, 19, of Canoga Park and Maurice Jones, 19, of Panorama City were 
arrested Thursday in connection with the death of Timothy Walls three days 
earlier, Detective Al Ferrand said. 
</P>
<P>
Walls, 20, of Pacoima was shot Monday night while standing at Van Nuys 
Boulevard and Borden Avenue in Pacoima, police said. A 17-year-old Pacoima boy, 
whose name was not disclosed, was seriously wounded. 
</P>
<P>
Ferrand would not discuss how detectives identified Johnson and Jones as 
suspects in the shooting. 
</P>
