</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Times pompously declares in its Nov. 2 editorial that the Herald Examiner 
folded, in part, because "the public's appetite for such reportage is satisfied 
by lesser television talk shows." In this same editorial phrases such as 
"working-class tastes" and "entertaining sensationalism of yellow journalism" 
are used. This display of arrogant elitism will make the loss of the Herald all 
the more painful. 
</P>
<P>
