<HEADLINE>
<P>
L.A. POLICE NAB BETTING BOWLERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
We have double locks on our doors and an alarm system. There is a mercury vapor 
light that illuminates the front of our house at night. We have a 12-gauge 
shotgun at the ready. My wife and daughter rarely venture out of the house at 
night by themselves. 
</P>
<P>
After reading about the "bust" of the Granada Hills women bowlers, I know I am 
paranoid. If our law enforcement people have the crime situation so under 
control that assets can be used to break up the threats to society that side 
bets in bowling can create, I know that I must reassess my feelings about crime 
in Los Angeles. Certainly there should be no reason for my family not to sleep 
soundly at night! 
</P>
<P>
CHARLES T. OSTERMEYER, Los Angeles 
</P>
