<HEADLINE>
<P>
JUVENILES TO MEET IN LOS ALAMITOS RACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Flomont, the Ed Burke Memorial Futurity winner, and Way Maker, who won the Dash 
For Cash Futurity, face off Saturday night in the $448,500 Golden State 
Futurity at Los Alamitos. 
</P>
<P>
The race is the third meeting of the 2-year-olds, and should decide the 
juvenile championship of the Horsemen's Quarter Horse Racing Assn. meeting. 
</P>
<P>
The race has attracted a field of 10. In post position order, they are: Tic Tac 
Oh with jockey Eddie Garcia; Flomont (James Lackey); Shake Six (Kip 
Didericksen); The Mogul (James Brooks); On The Hustle (Henry Garcia); Pie Glass 
(Kenneth Hart); Debonaire Kid (Joe Meier); Way Maker (Danny Cardoza); 
Sheisabedouin (Ralph Pauline); and American Farmer (Roman Figueroa). 
</P>
<P>
Way Maker is the leading money earner in this field with $348,311. In his 
12-race career, he has won four races including the Governor's Cup Futurity. 
Flomont has won $220,090 in her 11-race career. 
</P>
</TEXT>
