<P>
HOLTVILLE BEATS IMPERIAL, ENDS SEASON PERFECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Holtville finished the regular season undefeated with a 34-13 victory over 
visiting Imperial Friday night. For the second consecutive year Holtville 
(10-0, 5-0) will make a 1-A playoff appearance. Holtville was defeated in the 
playoffs last year by Marian, which finished this season, 1-9, 2-4 and will 
move to 2-A next season. 
</P>
<P>
The Vikings, led by quarterback Alex Wells, will play Imperial (7-3, 4-1) in 
the playoffs. Wells is averaging 145 yards per game and was ninth in the county 
in passing this week. 
</P>
