<HEADLINE>
<P>
GARDENING; 
</P>
<P>
WEEKEND CHECKLIST FOR DIGGERS AND PLANTERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For dedicated gardeners, here are suggestions from the California Assn. of 
Nurserymen: 
</P>
<P>
Ask a nurseryman now for the correct spray to use on your dormant plants to 
control pests and diseases. 
</P>
<P>
Plant cyclamen for an endless show of color during the coolest and wettest 
months of the year. 
</P>
<P>
Keep those annuals you planted last month well watered and be sure to feed them 
this month. 
</P>
<P>
House plants need less water as the days get shorter and skies grow dimmer, 
especially those in plastic pots (which don't breathe like clay pots); keep an 
eye on those near the fireplace or heater, though. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA111189-0062 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 133274 </DOCID>
