<TEXT>
<P>
Soviet Ambassador Yuri V. Dubinin announced in Washington the largest art 
exchange program ever between the United States and the Soviet Union. At least 
a dozen museums in each country, plus one in Canada, will participate in the 
five-year program. Paintings and art works from both countries will range from 
the Middle Ages to the present. The exchanges are being sponsored by the 
American non-profit group Intercultura and the Soviet Ministry of Culture. 
</P>
