<TEXT>
<P>
In an effort to control rowdy soccer fans, organizers of the 1990 World Cup may 
make England play its initial matches in Sicily. 
</P>
<P>
Italian organizers indicated this week that the English team is likely to play 
in Palermo, organizing committee sources said. 
</P>
<P>
World Cup games will be played in 12 Italian cities and the most popular teams 
are expected to play in Rome, Milan, Verona and Turin. 
</P>
<P>
Also, AEK Athens was banned for one season from European Club competition and 
Real Madrid was fined $125,000 by the Union of European Football Associations, 
governing body of European soccer, for fan rowdiness and player misconduct. 
