<TEXT>
<P>
Leading rusher John Johnson and starting cornerback Roderick Jones of the 
Ventura College football team were shot late Thursday at a Moorpark shopping 
center. 
</P>
<P>
Johnson and Jones, both of Oxnard, had attended a Moorpark High football game 
and were in a Moorpark shopping center when they were injured by an apparently 
random shotgun blast fired from a passing car. 
</P>
<P>
Both players will miss the remainder of the season, including today's Western 
State Conference game against Moorpark College. Johnson has three pellets in 
his legs, and Jones has one pellet in his leg. 
</P>
