<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE: SUND IS NEW CHIEF OF UNIT OWNED BY TIMES MIRROR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jeffrey O. Sund has been named president and chief executive of Richard D. 
Irwin Inc., a college business and economics textbook publisher owned by Times 
Mirror. The appointment is effective Nov. 27. 
</P>
<P>
 Sund most recently served as vice president and editorial director of college 
publishing at Houghton Mifflin. He joined that company in 1973, serving in a 
variety of positions including editor-in-chief of its business and science 
department, college division. Before joining Houghton Mifflin, he was a sales 
representative for Prentice-Hall for six years. 
</P>
<P>
Richard D. Irwin Inc. is based in Homewood, Ill. Times Mirror is a media and 
information company based in Los Angeles and also publishes the Los Angeles 
Times. 
</P>
</TEXT>
