<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOODBRIDGE KEEPS COSTA MESA WINLESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
IRVINE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Woodbridge High School scored the game's first four touchdowns and coasted to a 
29-14 Pacific Coast League victory over winless Costa Mesa Friday night at 
Irvine Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
Steve Madden scored scored twice, the first from two yards out with 4:32 left 
in the first quarter for Woodbridge (4-6, 2-3). 
</P>
<P>
Scott Seymour then ran 38 yards with an interception with 2:12 remaining in the 
second quarter. Seymour also ran for the two-point conversion to increase the 
lead to 15-0. 
</P>
<P>
Woodbridge made it 22-0 lead when quarterback Gary Fishel connected with Gary 
Gibson on a 28-yard touchdown pass with :22 left in the first half. 
</P>
<P>
Madden's seven-yard touchdown run with 8:47 remaining in the third quarter gave 
Woodbridge a 29-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
Costa Mesa (0-10, 0-5) scored on a two-yard touchdown run by Mike Webster and a 
successful two-point conversion by quarterback Mike Cutler with 6:33 left in 
the game, and Webster scored again from 10 yards out with 1:06 remaining. 
</P>
</TEXT>
