<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANCICH LEADS TUSTIN PAST UNIVERSITY, 14-10 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TUSTIN 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Powered by fullback Visko Ancich's 143 yards, Tustin High School (7-3 overall, 
4-1 league) earned sole possession of second place in the Sea View League and a 
Southern Section playoff berth with a 14-10 victory over University High School 
(2-8, 0-5) Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
The Tillers scored first when quarterback Andy Borza hit Chad Smith with a 
22-yard touchdown pass after Tustin recovered a Trojan fumble at its own 47. 
</P>
<P>
University tied the score, 7-7, when Victor Davis rambled 40 yards for a 
touchdown on a screen pass from Brian Vail early in the second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Then Ancich broke loose for a 66-yard run that set up a Borza one-yard 
touchdown run, giving the Tillers a 14-7 edge, but the Trojans answered with a 
22-yard David Jacobson field goal to make it 14-10 just before the half. 
</P>
<P>
Tustin could not relax until University failed to score on a fourth and goal on 
the Tiller seven with 2:30 left. The Tillers stopped Jerry Apana at the three 
on a short pass, denying the Trojans their first league victory of the year. 
MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
