<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
US Facilities Corp.: The Costa Mesa-based insurance company reported net income 
for the third quarter of $307,000, contrasted with a year-earlier loss of $1.2 
million. Revenue rose 54%, to $16.4 million from $10.6 million. For the 
nine-month period, net income rose to $1.3 million from a loss of $1.7 million 
for the comparable 1988 quarters. Revenue increased 57%, to $45.4 million from 
$29 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Corporate Earnings 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA111189-0121 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 133424 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
November 11, 1989, Saturday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Business; Part D; Page 6; Column 4; Financial Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
164 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS: SANTA ANA'S EECO REPORTS $4.1 MILLION FOR 3RD QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
EECO Inc., a Santa Ana-based manufacturer, reported net income of $4.1 million 
for the third quarter ended Oct. 1, contrasted with net income of $255,000 for 
the like period a year ago. The 1989 quarter includes a gain of $6.8 million 
from the previously reported sale of its Avionics business. Sales dropped 34%, 
to $10.5 million from $15.7 million. 
</P>
<P>
The company lost $612,000 for the first three quarters of the year, contrasted 
with net income of $286,000 in 1988. Year-to-date sales for 1989 declined 19%, 
to $37.9 million from $46.9 million. 
</P>
<P>
EECO attributed the lower sales levels in 1989 to price erosion in the keyboard 
business and a decline in volume in all its businesses due to the inability to 
meet customer demand. That was caused by disruptions resulting from facility 
moves and inadequate material planning and control, the company said. 
</P>
<P>
EECO manufactures computer keyboards, electronic key pads, electromechanical 
switches and hotel computer systems worldwide. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Corporate Earnings 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA111189-0122 </DOCNO>
