FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TWA earnings -- An item in Friday's earnings column incorrectly stated the 
third-quarter results of Trans World Airlines. The airline company reported a 
net loss of $29.9 million, contrasted with a profit of $88 million in the same 
period a year ago. Revenue was unchanged at $1.3 billion. The New York-based 
firm cited increased interest expenses and a non-recurring gain from litigation 
in the 1988 period. 
</P>
