<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO; 
</P>
<P>
AIRPORT GROUP ASKS FOR $5,200 DONATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council appears lukewarm over a funding request by an ad-hoc 
organization that has come under fire from South Orange County officials and 
landowners for considering the area as a possible site for a second regional 
airport. 
</P>
<P>
Clarence J. Turner, vice president of the Costa Mesa-based Airport Site 
Coalition, said he has asked Mission Viejo officials to donate $5,200 to the 
organization, which is experiencing fiscal problems. 
</P>
<P>
The funding request will be considered at the council's Monday night meeting, 
Mayor William S. Craycraft said on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
But Craycraft, who has repeatedly criticized the coalition for various 
proposals to build a regional airport in South County, said that he will 
recommend rejection. 
</P>
<P>
"If the coalition is bent on recommending a South Orange County site, I would 
strongly oppose that our city participate in funding the coalition," Craycraft 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The Airport Site Coalition began 19 months ago to narrow a list of 31 proposed 
airport sites. A second airport site is being sought as a way to relieve 
traffic problems and airplane congestion at John Wayne Airport, Turner said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
